    <h1>2017-09-22 Meeting about item-level security alternative</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"id-2017-09-22Meetingaboutitem-levelsecurityalternative-Bu=
sinessrules:">Business rules:</h2>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>if user A has shared item with user B, then user B cannot share this it=
em with any other user</li>
<li>items can only be shared with USERS not with companies</li>
<li>definition of item that can be shared:
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>dashboard</li>
<li>filter</li>
<li><s>scheduled task</s>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>this cannot be shared because it would make no sense: a user can easily=
 create a scheduled task himself (as opposed to a dashboard)</li>
</ul></li>
<li>report</li>
</ul></li>
<li>a filter is always shared view-only, never edit</li>
<li>a dashboard can be shared:
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>view-only</li>
<li>edit</li>
</ul></li>
<li>when a dashboard is shared, the sharer has to indicate if the underlyin=
g (raw) data is also shared.
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>if the underlying data is shared, then the filter is visible in the fil=
ter overview (the filter is also shared). else: not, only the dashboard is =
shared</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-2017-09-22Meetingaboutitem-levelsecurityalternative-Scenarios"=
>Scenarios</h2>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>scenario 1
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>user A shares dashboard 1 with user B</li>
<li>dashboard 1 is based on filter F1</li>
<li>user B creates filter F2 based on filter F1</li>
<li>user A modifies F1</li>
<li>what happens?</li>
</ul></li>
<li>scenario 2
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>same as 1 but user A DELETES F1</li>
<li>what happens?</li>
</ul></li>
<li>scenario 3
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>user U1 shares dashboard D1 with user U2</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>dashboard D1 is based on filter F1</li>
<li>user U2 creates filter F2 based on filter F1</li>
<li>user U2 shares dashboard D2 with user U3</li>
<li>dashboard D2 is based on filter F2</li>
<li>user U3 creates filter F3 based on filter F2</li>
<li>etc. Un, Fn, Dn</li>
<li>user U1 modifies F1</li>
<li>what happens?</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-2017-09-22Meetingaboutitem-levelsecurityalternative-Questions"=
>Questions</h2>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>should we define the relationship between asset and company? (owner, re=
ader, ...)
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>who can add/edit static properties?</li>
</ul></li>
<li>to be investigated
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>when the user wants to share a filter: how to specify the sharee?</li>
<li>system shows a list of users?
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>SL: no, we cannot show list of users</li>
</ul></li>
<li>user has to enter emailaddress
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>system cannot say if address belongs to RAS user</li>
</ul></li>
<li>...</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
